## TL;DR: What Every 1ct Cushion Buyer Must Know First

The 1 carat cushion cut diamond ring is the most accessible, most inventory-rich entry in the cushion cut market. Natural 1ct GIA cushion diamonds at Blue Nile start at $1,891 for a G-VS1 Ideal — competitive, abundant, and immediately available. At 6.5mm × 6.5mm face-up, the 1ct cushion is proportionate on most hands, distinctively soft-cornered versus a round, and the size where The Modified Brilliant Split — the choice between crushed ice and chunky facets — is most visible to buyers comparing side by side in a jeweller's case.

**Contrarian Truth — The Modified Brilliant Split at 1ct:** Most buyers searching for a 1ct cushion cut will be shown cushion modified brilliants. This is not the only option. The cushion brilliant sub-type (GIA cert reads "Cushion" not "Cushion Modified") produces larger, more distinct facet flashes and visible fire that the modified brilliant's crushed ice pattern cannot match. At 1ct, the visual difference between these two sub-types is clearly visible at normal viewing distance — more so than at any smaller size. The Modified Brilliant Split is the most important decision in the 1ct cushion market, and most buyers do not know it exists when they begin shopping.

