## What Is a 1 Carat Cushion Cut Diamond Ring?

A 1 carat cushion cut diamond ring centres a 1ct cushion-shaped diamond — approximately 6.5mm × 6.5mm in standard square proportions — in an engagement ring setting. At 1ct, the cushion cut is the most commonly purchased size in this shape: it is large enough to read clearly as a cushion (the soft corners are visible and distinctive), small enough to wear comfortably on any hand, and priced accessibly enough to allow meaningful quality choices within a reasonable budget.

I'm **Farzana Hasan**, a GIA Expert. The [1 carat cushion cut](/cushion-cut-diamond) is where most cushion buyers begin their diamond education — and where The Modified Brilliant Split causes the most confusion. At 1ct, the natural market has abundant inventory, competitive pricing, and full choice across colour-clarity combinations. Unlike the [2 carat cushion cut diamond ring](/2-carat-cushion-cut-diamond-ring) where carat weight psychology increases pressure and The Pillow Premium becomes a significant dollar figure, the 1ct cushion market is buyer-friendly: you have choices, you have time, and the decision is primarily about quality priorities rather than scarcity management.

What determines whether a 1ct cushion purchase succeeds: choosing the right sub-type before you choose anything else (modified brilliant or cushion brilliant — The Modified Brilliant Split), understanding The Pillow Premium at 1ct (small in absolute dollars but real), and matching the setting — halo versus solitaire, rose gold versus white gold — to the intended look before committing to the center stone size.

Full credentials and methodology at **[Diamond Critics](https://diamondcritics.com/about-farzana/)**.

