## The Pillow Premium

The Pillow Premium — the systematic cost premium cushion cuts carry over princess cuts of equivalent quality — is present at 1ct but small in absolute dollar terms. A GIA 1ct G-VS1 Ideal princess cut at Blue Nile runs approximately $1,600–$1,700. The GIA 1ct G-VS1 Ideal cushion modified brilliant starts at $1,891 — a premium of $200–$300, or approximately 12–18%.

[![Cushion cut diamond engagement ring in rose gold solitaire with pavé band](https://ion.bluenile.com/sets/Jewelry/Photoshoot/Bluenile/BrioSuperImposeBox/Rings/502250/502250_M1_CSH_DIM_wht_0100CT_Y_Box3_004_1600X1600.jpg)](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings?ShapeID=Cushion&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)

At 1ct, The Pillow Premium is manageable and should not drive the purchase decision away from the cushion if that is the preferred shape. The absolute premium of $200–$300 is meaningful but not prohibitive — unlike at 3ct or 4ct natural, where The Pillow Premium adds $5,000–$30,000 over a comparable princess cut.

**Why The Pillow Premium exists at 1ct.** Cushion cuts require rough crystal material in slightly different proportions than princess cuts, and cushion rough yields vary. More importantly, the sustained consumer preference for cushion over princess at 1ct creates pricing power for the cushion shape across all retail channels. The premium is not irrational from a market perspective — it reflects what buyers consistently pay more for.

**The Pillow Premium in the lab market at 1ct.** In the lab 1ct cushion market, The Pillow Premium is minimal to non-existent. Lab production of 1ct cushion modified brilliants is highly efficient, and shape-based pricing differentials that exist in the natural market largely disappear in lab production. For buyers choosing between lab cushion and lab princess at 1ct, the price difference is negligible — the choice is purely aesthetic.

For a full analysis of how The Pillow Premium scales from 1ct through 5ct, see the [2 carat cushion cut diamond ring guide](/2-carat-cushion-cut-diamond-ring) where the premium first becomes a significant dollar figure.

