## 1ct Cushion Clarity: VS2 vs VS1

At 1ct, the clarity question is more forgiving than at larger sizes — the 6.5mm face-up area is small enough that most VS2 and many SI1 inclusions are not visible to the naked eye in a cushion modified brilliant. However, the advice to drop to SI1 "because cushion modified brilliants hide inclusions" applies with more caution at certain stone types.

**VS1 at 1ct.** VS1 at 1ct in any cushion sub-type is reliably eye-clean without video verification. At $1,891 for a G-VS1 Ideal, VS1 is available at the entry price. There is no compelling reason to drop below VS1 at 1ct when the entry stone is already VS1.

**VS2 at 1ct.** VS2 in a 1ct cushion modified brilliant is typically eye-clean — the crushed ice facet pattern scatters light effectively around most VS2-grade inclusions at 6.5mm face-up. VS2 savings versus VS1 at 1ct are $100–$300, which is meaningful only at very tight budgets. If budget requires VS2, request the HD video, check the GIA plot for inclusion type (feather and crystal inclusions are more visible than needles), and confirm eye-cleanliness before purchasing.

**SI1 at 1ct cushion modified brilliant.** SI1 at 1ct in a cushion modified brilliant can be eye-clean but requires video confirmation. The modified brilliant at 6.5mm hides some SI1 inclusions effectively, but poorly-positioned SI1 inclusions can be visible. SI1 is not recommended as a clarity floor for 1ct cushion purchases unless the specific stone has been HD video-confirmed as eye-clean by the buyer — not just described as "eye-clean" by the retailer.

